On the circle, with statements A (uniform $\to f$), B ($L^2$ $\to f$), C ($S[f](0)\to f(0)=1$), D (Cesàro sum at $0$ equals $f(0)=1$), classify:
(1) $f$ Riemann integrable, $\lim_{x\to0}f=f(0)=1$;
(2) as (1) and $f'(0)$ exists;
(3) $f\in C(\mathbb S)$, $f(0)=1$, $\sum_n|\hat f(n)|<\infty$;
(4) $f=\mathbf 1_{[-\pi,0]}$.
